							<figcaption class="imageCaption">Bori Péterfy the singer holding “2B” vinyl (via her <a href="https://www.instagram.com/peterfybori/" data-href="https://www.instagram.com/peterfybori/" class="markup--anchor markup--figure-anchor" target="_blank">Instagram</a>&nbsp;account)</figcaption>
						</figure>
						<p name="98ba" id="98ba" class="graf--p graf-after--figure">
						<strong class="markup--strong markup--p-strong">Ambrus:</strong> As “2B” was a back catalog release, I guess the key was that it was our first crowd funding vinyl project. The first one is always more appealing than the next ones! Even with a large fan base, it is really hard to convince people to buy vinyl.</p>
						<p name="f7d3" id="f7d3" class="graf--p graf-after--p">
						<strong class="markup--strong markup--p-strong">QRATES:</strong> What is your impression of the quality of the pressing?</p>
						<p name="1dc8" id="1dc8" class="graf--p graf-after--p">
						<strong class="markup--strong markup--p-strong">Ambrus:</strong> It was really good. The new one will be even better because we are pressing it on 180-gram vinyl. Unlike last time, we did special mastering for vinyl, last time we didn’t have access to the masters.</p>
					
					
					
